parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Gauge Inaccuracy and Engine Stalling
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inaccurate fuel gauge can lead to unexpected engine stalling, which can cause accidents, especially on busy highways, and leave drivers stranded.
symptoms: Erratic fuel gauge movement
fuel gauge reading incorrectly
engine stalling
sudden loss of power
vehicle unable to restart
"check engine" light illumination.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fan control module can cause the engine to overheat, leading to potential engine damage, fire, or even total loss of the vehicle. This can also cause the air conditioner to stop working, making the vehicle uncomfortable and potentially unsafe to drive.
symptoms: Hot air blows from the air vents when the air conditioning is activated
the engine overheating warning indicator illuminates
the air conditioner fails
and several warning indicators illuminate on the instrument panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An engine fire can cause significant damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to total loss, and may also pose a risk to the safety of the occupants and other road users.
symptoms: The engine catches on fire
resulting in significant damage or total loss of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of door latches and mirrors can cause doors to open while driving, leading to accidents or injuries, and also create a safety hazard when exiting the vehicle.
symptoms: Door latches quit working
doors cannot be secured when the vehicle is stationary
doors can latch but locks do not engage when starting the vehicle
passenger and driver side mirrors falling or flying off the mount while in motion
rear door not catching when fully open and automatically closing in rapid motion.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the AM radio transmission/reception can prevent drivers from receiving important emergency alerts and traffic reports, potentially putting them at risk.
symptoms: AM radio quits working
unable to tune to local area stations for emergency traffic reports
unable to receive national emergency alerts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent appearance of SRS airbag warning lights can cause confusion and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: SRS airbag warning lights appear randomly or for no reason
SRS airbag warning lights turn off
SRS airbag warning lights appear upon starting the car.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Battery failure and electrical faults can cause safety hazards, including the risk of electrical shock, and can also lead to other system failures.
symptoms: Battery failure caused by open low current short
electrical faults during routine maintenance inspections
unknown electrical problems that can be life-threatening.
